We found that using biased datasets lead to an overestimation of an LM's performance for fact prediction. To neither over- nor underestimate BERT's performance, we tested it on the large dataset \ourdataset{} and implemented improvements to increase BERT's performance and perform KBC with high precision later on. We have seen the model's vocabulary to be a bottleneck for its performance. When fine-tuning with vocabulary extension, the model's performance can be significantly improved for fact prediction.